The paper discusses architectural approaches for constructing dependable learning-enabled autonomous systems, with a focus on automated driving. This involves the use of diverse redundancy, information fusion, and runtime monitoring, which are all relevant to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), and systems engineering (cs.SE) for autonomous systems. Additionally, the paper discusses recent architectural approaches for increasing the dependability of learning-enabled components beyond standard convolutional neural networks, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and systems engineering (cs.SY).
